Subject: [PATCH] Redirect legacy opal-blog/ posts to their new /blog/
 equivalents

Fixes the cannibalization risk flagged in the SEO review: the 9 old
Squarespace-era opal-blog/ posts were orphaned (no nav links) but still
indexed and overlapping topically with the new evidence-based batch.
301-redirects each to its closest topical match (new blog post, or the
relevant service/concern page where no single post matches), plus the
opal-blog/ index to /blog/. Also drops all 10 opal-blog URLs from
sitemap.xml so they stop being resubmitted for re-crawl.

Old posts had zero ranking keywords per Ahrefs, so nothing lost by
redirecting now; any residual link equity consolidates into the
current pages instead.
